<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-108] sync implementation reorders operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-108</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current implementation of sync is broken. There is a race condition that causes a follower to return operations out of order, causing clients to drop their connections to a server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll be attaching a patch to fix this problem shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12401452">ZOOKEEPER-108</key>
            <summary>sync implementation reorders operations</summary>
